filter_factor_levels_by_missing.Rd

removes measurments with less than percent=60 missing values in factor_level = 1

filter_factor_levels_by_missing(pdata, config, percent = 60)

Arguments

pdata

data.frame
config

AnalysisConfiguration

Value

data.frame

Examples


rm(list=ls())
library(prolfqua)
library(tidyverse)
bb <- prolfqua::data_spectronautDIA250_A
config <- bb$config_f()
analysis <- bb$analysis(bb$data, bb$config_f())

#> creating sampleName
#> completing cases
config$parameter$min_nr_of_notNA  <- 20
data <- analysis
data <- removeLarge_Q_Values(data, config)
hierarchy_counts(data, config)

#> # A tibble: 1 x 5
#>   Isotope.Label protein_Id peptide_Id modPeptide_Id precursor_Id
#>   <chr>              <int>      <int>         <int>        <int>
#> 1 Light                 50        436           651          823
res <- filter_factor_levels_by_missing(data, config,percent = 60)

#> completing cases
#> Joining, by = c("protein_Id", "peptide_Id", "modPeptide_Id", "precursor_Id")
data1 <-complete_cases(data, config)

#> completing cases
hierarchy_counts(res, config)

#> # A tibble: 1 x 5
#>   Isotope.Label protein_Id peptide_Id modPeptide_Id precursor_Id
#>   <chr>              <int>      <int>         <int>        <int>
#> 1 Light                 49        382           570          708
summarize_hierarchy(res,config) %>%
 dplyr::filter(!!sym(paste0(config$table$hierarchyKeys()[2],"_n")) > 1)
